<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; HOURS EXTENDED FOR VOTER REGISTRATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city clerk will extend office hours today to allow voters more time to 
register for the June 7 primary elections. 
</P>
<P>
 City Clerk Connie Brockway said that her office will stay open until 8 p.m. 
for today's voter registration deadline. Voters may register at City Hall's 
lower level near the council chambers, 2000 Main St., she said. Brockway said 
that regular registration is from 8 a.m. to 5 p.m. Monday through Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Citizens 18 years or older also may register by mail, she said. The registrar 
of voters' office will stay open until midnight tonight to accommodate those 
who want to register.BERT ELJERA 
</P>
