<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; HEARING PLANNED ON WATER FEE PROPOSAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Ventura City Council will hold a hearing Monday on raising residential 
water and sewage fees by 7% in the 1994-95 fiscal year, which begins July 1. 
</P>
<P>
 A median city household spends about $75.25 on water and sewage every two 
months. The ordinance under consideration by the council would raise that bill 
by $4.91. 
</P>
<P>
 The fee increases would pay for higher operating costs and future water and 
sewer projects. A limited amount would also pay for a low-interest loan program 
to help businesses invest in a sanitation pre-treatment operation that would 
lower overall sanitation costs. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council meeting begins at 7:30 p.m. at Ventura City Hall, 501 Poli 
St., Ventura. CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
