<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: VENTURA COLLEGE JOB FAIRE SET WEDNESDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 More than five dozen companies are scheduled to participate in the Ventura 
College Job Faire, an annual career day that attracts hundreds of students and 
employers from throughout Ventura County. 
</P>
<P>
 The job fair will be held from 10 a.m. to 2:30 p.m. Wednesday in the quad area 
of the Ventura campus. 
</P>
<P>
 "The fair is designed to give employers a wide cross-section of area residents 
interested in employment opportunities," said Rheda Gomberg, a career resources 
specialist at Ventura College. 
</P>
<P>
 "People come from as far north as Santa Barbara and as far south as the San 
Fernando Valley," she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Companies such as Kinko's Service Corp., Packard Bell and Farmers Insurance 
have agreed to participate, as have numerous local retailers and service 
industries. 
</P>
<P>
 Job fair organizers are seeking more local firms that may be looking to hire. 
Employers will be asked to bring job applications and job descriptions. 
</P>
<P>
 Tables and chairs will be provided for displays and a continental breakfast 
and buffet lunch also will be offered at no charge to participating employers. 
</P>
<P>
 Employers who wish to sign up for the Ventura College Job Faire should contact 
Gomberg at (805) 654-6489. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
