<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Ken Williams 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Fullerton Museum Center is calling for collectors to bring in sample items 
from their stashes as documentation for a forthcoming exhibition examining the 
collecting impulse. Collectors of "anything and everything" are asked to bring 
the museum one sample (the object or a photo of it), plus a written description 
of the collection, between 3 and 7 p.m. on May 17.The sample items will be 
photographed and the collector will be interviewed. Objects need not be left at 
the museum; collectors may be contacted later regarding loans for the 
exhibition. The show, "Gotta Have It!," will open in December. (714) 738-6545. 
</P>
<P>
 The Orange Art Assn. will have its first art competition, juried by Fullerton 
College art professor Julia Beardsley, on July 22 from 6 to 9 p.m. and July 23 
from 9 a.m. to noon. Artists working in traditional or modern styles may bring 
their two- or three-dimensional work (no slides) to the Guggenheim Gallery at 
Chapman University on either date. The exhibition will be at the gallery Aug. 
3-21. Prizes include Best of Show ($200) and First, Second, Third and Popular 
Choice for both two-dimensional and sculptural work. $5 per entry for members, 
$8 for non-members. (714) 551-9476. 
</P>
