<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: WESTMINSTER; HEARING TONIGHT ON STATUS OF 3 SCHOOLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Westminster School District will hold a public hearing tonight to hear 
public views on whether to declare two elementary schools and part of a third 
campus surplus. 
</P>
<P>
 The district Property Advisory Committee is considering selling or leasing 
Virginia K. Boos Elementary and James W. Franklin Elementary and a 10-acre 
portion of Finley Elementary, spokeswoman Audrey Brown said. 
</P>
<P>
 The committee will make its recommendation to the school board in the next few 
months. After holding its own hearing, the full board will make its decision. 
</P>
<P>
 To optimize the number of students at schools throughout the district, the 
Board of Education voted this year to close Boos and Franklin in June, Brown 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Surplus sites may be sold or leased at the board's discretion, and each site 
will be considered individually, Brown said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Finley site is at 13521 Edwards St. Franklin is at 14422 Hammon Lane in 
Huntington Beach. The hearing will be held at 7 p.m. at Boos, 13890 Hammon 
Place, in Westminster. JON NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
