<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE SEEK GUNMAN WHO ROBBED BANK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By VIVIEN LOU CHEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A masked gunman robbed a Wells Fargo Bank at 13300 Riverside Drive over the 
weekend and fled through an alley with an undisclosed amount of money, police 
said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The man entered the bank about 1:30 p.m. Saturday, wearing a black mask and a 
white sweat shirt with a black hood, said Officer Cathryn Delvecchio of the Los 
Angeles Police Department's Van Nuys station. 
</P>
<P>
 One of the bank's tellers handed the robber a dye pack hidden among the money, 
she said. A dye pack is a security device intended to explode and stain the 
bills. VIVIEN LOU CHEN 
</P>
</TEXT>
