<HEADLINE>
<P>
ACCIDENT KILLS 2 ON ANTELOPE VALLEY FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By VIVIEN LOU CHEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two people were killed early Sunday after the car in which they were riding 
swerved out of control and flipped over several times, ejecting the occupants 
on the southbound Antelope Valley Freeway near Newhall, the California Highway 
Patrol said. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities have not determined what caused the accident and did not release 
the names of the two victims riding in the car, pending notification of next of 
kin. 
</P>
<P>
 A third unidentified person had been in the car as a passenger and was taken 
to a San Fernando Valley hospital with massive injuries. 
</P>
<P>
 None of the three were wearing seat belts and all were ejected from the car 
when it failed to make a left-hand turn just south of Escondido Canyon Road, 
said CHP Officer Frank Lewis. The car swerved into the right shoulder and 
flipped over several times. VIVIEN LOU CHEN 
</P>
</TEXT>
