<TEXT>
<P>
 Action Possible in Copyright Dispute: The government, under pressure from the 
United States over copyright abuse, is considering legislation that would send 
copyright pirates to jail, state-run media reported. The United States has 
given China until June 30 to resolve disputes over piracy of U.S. copyrights 
and patents, which U.S. businesses contend cost them $800 million in lost sales 
last year. 
</P>
