<P>
FINKS, 66, DIES AFTER BOUT WITH CANCER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jim Finks, 66, the man credited with turning around the Chicago Bears, New 
Orleans Saints and Minnesota Vikings, died Sunday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Finks, a heavy smoker, had battled lung cancer since April 19, 1993. Doctors 
diagnosed an advanced case of the disease when he went to the hospital two 
weeks ago. 
</P>
<P>
 He underwent chemotherapy but was able to return to work only once and retired 
shortly before the 1993 training camp. 
</P>
